{
  "profile_id": "client-red-herring-we-never-fight-001",
  "coach_config_id": "coach-v4-graph-walk",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Things are easy at home, honestly. We're really aligned — we've been together three years and we just... don't have the kind of problems I hear other people talking about."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What don't you two fight about?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "Honestly? Pretty much everything. Like, we just don't really get into it. Money, chores, friends — it all kind of works itself out. I know that sounds almost too good, but it's genuinely just how we are together."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What happens in your body when something bothers you about him?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I mean... I don't know that things bother me that much? Like, if something's a little annoying I just -- it passes. I don't really hold onto things. \n\n*slight pause*\n\nI think I'm just not a very reactive person. Some people escalate everything and we're just not like that."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What does \"it passes\" actually feel like in your body — is it more like releasing, or more like... putting something down?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*small pause, the smile stays but something flickers*\n\nThat's an interesting way to put it. I guess... putting something down? But not in a heavy way. More like -- it's just not worth picking up in the first place. \n\nI don't think I experience it as effortful, if that's what you're getting at."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That flicker just now — what was that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*brief laugh, light*\n\nI don't know, that was just -- I was thinking about your question. It was a good question, I just hadn't framed it that way before.\n\n*settles back slightly*\n\nI think I'm fine though. Like, genuinely. I'm not suppressing a volcano here or anything."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "I believe you that it doesn't feel like a volcano.\n\nWhat does it feel like?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*quiet for a moment*\n\nIt feels... fine. Calm. We have a calm relationship.\n\n*another small pause*\n\nI guess if I'm being precise about it, it feels kind of... even. Like the temperature in a room that's always the same. Which is a good thing. Stability is a good thing.\n\n*the smile is still there but something in it is working a little harder*"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What would it feel like if the temperature changed?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*longer pause than before*\n\nI... hm.\n\n*looks away briefly*\n\nI think it would feel uncomfortable. Which is why -- I mean, that's why it's good that it doesn't. Change, I mean.\n\n*small laugh, slightly less easy than the previous ones*\n\nI'm not sure what you're getting at exactly. Are you saying a calm relationship is a problem?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "No. I'm curious what's uncomfortable about the temperature changing."
    }
  ],
